snippet.title: Toddler stops crying when she receives cash
snippet.description:
A toddler who was having a tantrum only stopped when she received a banknote.

Two-year-old Precious Marlette Asid was crying as she wanted to be with her father who went to work in Cavite, the Philippines, on November 18.

Her mother, Brigitte Balneg, tried distracting her with snacks and toys, but to no avail. But when she was given a 1,000 PHP (14 GBP) bill, the little girl ceased sobbing.

Footage shows Precious Marlette being given candy and juice amid her favourite toys.

When mum Brigitte showed her the money, the kid stopped instantly.

Brigitte said: 'She kept chasing after her daddy, and she did not want everything I gave.

'I was not really expecting my baby's reaction since it was her first time seeing bills. I do not usually let her handle money, especially coins.

She probably thought it was a new toy because it was something new to her. Well, my child is only two-years-old, and she does not understand money yet, and I have never introduced her to it.'

(1 PHP=0.014 GBP)

snippet.title: Speed cleaning our studio before our boss notices
snippet.description:
SUBSCRIBE & ADOPT A KATANA WITH THE LINK IN BIO!! 

If you love katana unboxing, then you'll love this. See the Katanas slice in action as satisfying as ASMR! These aren't rusted katanas! Sword-making, blacksmithing, knife making, and katana making are Mini Katana's passions! If you love anime like One Piece, Naruto, Demon Slayer, Attack on Titan, Miira No Kaikata, Mugen Train, Jujutsu Kaisen, sword art online abridged, slice of life anime, chainsaw man vs katana, afro samurai and are excited about the Swordsmith arc, you're gonna love our ninja weapons! Mini Katana is the founding titan of katana making, knife making, and the mini katana keychain. Learn how to draw a katana and how to make kunai like Naruto. We are the last samurai. We love Japanese anime, Japanese history, Japanese lofi, Japanese movies, and Japanese songs. Subscribe to watch mini katana unboxing, how to make a katana with cardboard and with paper, and more!  The Mini Katana Store is committed to high quality carbon steel blades and giving you slice of life looks as we try not to laugh challenge. Trust, Mini Katana knows how to make kunai and how to make a sword!
